<subSubSection id="9EA2B0F7777BC32554BE4B355699DA58" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="D607E37C777BC32554BE4B355699DA58" blockId="3.[151,638,194,713]" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">
<emphasis id="E4CC3F6E777BC32554BE4B355750DA73" bold="true" box="[175,290,327,348]" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name refers to its similarity to 
<taxonomicName id="11B898FF777BC32554864B135697DA58" box="[151,229,353,375]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Brachys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rileyi">
<emphasis id="E4CC3F6E777BC32554864B135697DA58" box="[151,229,353,375]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">B. rileyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9EA2B0F7777BC32554BE4B0E5701D9E6" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="D607E37C777BC32554BE4B0E5701D9E6" blockId="3.[151,638,194,713]" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">
<emphasis id="E4CC3F6E777BC32554BE4B0E5753DABE" bold="true" box="[175,289,380,401]" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Discussion.</emphasis>
This species is superficially very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="11B898FF777BC32555124BE45724DA83" box="[259,342,406,428]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Brachys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rileyi">
<emphasis id="E4CC3F6E777BC32555124BE45724DA83" box="[259,342,406,428]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">B. rileyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and is therefore not figured separately; in fact, before I examined the 
<collectingRegion id="147C2D9E777BC32556544BC2540CDAEA" box="[581,638,432,453]" country="United States of America" name="Texas" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Texas</collectingRegion>
specimens and only saw the photograph (
<figureCitation id="4E83FFF9777BC32556254BB8541DDAF0" box="[564,623,458,479]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="1.[175,215,864,883]" captionTargetBox="[200,1123,204,840]" captionTargetId="figure-438@1.[151,1171,183,866]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs. 1–2. Brachys species, dorsal view. 1) B. rileyi; 2) B. barri." pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
), I thought it was conspecific. 
<taxonomicName id="11B898FF777BC32555D04B96540CDAD5" box="[449,638,484,506]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Brachys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="consimilis">
<emphasis id="E4CC3F6E777BC32555D04B96540CDAD5" box="[449,638,484,506]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">Brachys consimilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="11B898FF777BC325550A4B8C571CD93B" box="[283,366,510,532]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Brachys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rileyi">
<emphasis id="E4CC3F6E777BC325550A4B8C571CD93B" box="[283,366,510,532]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">B. rileyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
most obviously in having incomplete lateral carinae on the elytra; additionally, in 
<taxonomicName id="11B898FF777BC32554CF4840572BD967" box="[222,345,562,584]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Brachys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="224" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="consimilis">
<emphasis id="E4CC3F6E777BC32554CF4840572BD967" box="[222,345,562,584]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="224">B. consimilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the elytra are darker in coloration with two weak ridges on the disc and have separately rounded apices, the pronotum is reddish coppery and has the basal, transverse depression interrupted at the middle, and the head has dorsal, rounded protuberances.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
